1) Choose the math substrate

Let’s work over a field 𝔽 (ℝ for continuous, or ℚ/𝔽₂ if you want discrete-ish). Define these finite-dimensional vector spaces:
	•	E: entity space (basis vectors = entities)
	•	R: role space (basis vectors = roles)
	•	P: proposition/question space (basis vectors = atomic propositions / queries)
	•	C: conflict space
	•	G: goal space
	•	U: uncertainty space (can be 1D or multi-axis)
	•	K: invariant space (constraints)
	•	X: “world state” latent space (optional but helpful)

You can treat “meaning” as a representation choice: embeddings, one-hot, or learned basis.

