5) Admissibility and invariants (formal gate condition)

A beat is admissible iff it preserves invariants:

S' = b_S(S,T)
\phi_k(\Psi(S')) \le 0 \quad \forall k

And it is “productive” if it reduces expected tension:

\mathbb{E}\big[\|T'\|\big] \le \|T\| - \delta

for some \delta > 0 occurring at sufficient density (to prevent stagnation).

This is exactly where CogOS’s gate plugs in: your invariant check becomes the decision gate, but now it’s pure math.

