6) Closure (exact or approximate)

Exact closure

\exists n:\quad T_n = 0 \ \ \text{and}\ \ S_k \in \mathcal{S}_{feasible}\ \forall k\le n

Practical closure (better for real narratives/life)

\exists n:\quad \|T_n\| \le \varepsilon

with a residual tension certificate describing which subspace remains nonzero.

