7) NTE isomorphism (make it rigorous)

Two NTE instances N and N' are isomorphic if there exist invertible linear maps:

U_S:\mathcal{S}\to\mathcal{S}',\quad U_T:\mathcal{T}\to\mathcal{T}'

such that:
	1.	structure/tension correspond: U_S(S)=S', U_T(T)=T'
	2.	beats conjugate:

U \circ b \circ U^{-1} = b'

(where U acts on Y=\mathcal{S}\times\mathcal{T} blockwise)

This is clean: “a proof and a detective story are the same object” becomes “they are conjugate dynamical systems under representation change.”

